ding%20treats%20like%20dark%20chocolate%20and%20popcorn.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EForget%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-protein-guidelines-how-to-eat-more-without-too-much-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eproteinmaxxing%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20simple%20three-part%20rule%20can%20help%20you%20hit%20your%20goals%20without%20overdoing%20it%2C%20says%20a%20top%20nutritionist%20in%20the%20UK.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDominique%20Ludwig%20has%20been%20helping%20people%20eat%20healthfully%20for%20three%20decades.%20She%20said%20most%20diet%20trends%20offer%20contradictory%20advice%2C%20wasting%20your%20valuable%20time%2C%20money%2C%20and%20energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20a%20world%20where%20nutrition%20is%20very%20confusing%2C%20it%20can%20actually%20be%20really%20simple%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELudwig's%20new%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BNo%20Nonsense%20Nutrition%2C%26quot%3B%20offers%20a%20road%20map%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fweight-loss-doctor-simple-tip-eat-healthy-without-tracking-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehealthy%20eating%20principles%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20work%20for%20both%20her%20and%20her%20clients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20her%20favorite%20tips%20is%20the%20%26quot%3Btriple%2030%26quot%3B%20rule%3A%20eating%2030%20grams%20of%20protein%20at%20each%20meal%2C%2030%20grams%20of%20fiber%20each%20day%2C%20and%20at%20least%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feat-30-plants-week-fiber-gut-health-time-saving-habits-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E30%20different%20plants%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20your%20diet%20each%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELudwig%20said%20that%20within%20four%20weeks%20of%20following%20the%20triple%2030%20rule%2C%20her%20clients%20can%20cut%20back%20on%20processed%20foods%20without%20feeling%20deprived%20or%20relying%20on%20complex%20or%20strict%20eating%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20they%20often%20have%20reduced%20cravings%20and%20%26quot%3Bfood%20noise%2C%26quot%3B%20better%20digestion%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanti-inflammatory-foods-to-help-prevent-chronic-inflammation-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elower%20inflammation%3C%2Fa%3E%20(which%20may%20translate%20to%20fewer%20aches%20and%20pains)%2C%20better%20mood%2C%20and%20more%20energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSometimes%20you%20don't%20need%20to%20jump%20down%20every%20rabbit%20hole.%20If%20you%20just%20start%20with%20the%20foundation%2C%20you%20suddenly%20see%20that%20food%20actually%20can%20be%20one%20of%20the%20most%20transformational%20things%20we%20can%20do%20to%20our%20health%2C%26quot%3B%20Ludwig%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2270c37d06-8963-4500-a546-120e358041c2%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EEat%20protein%20at%20every%20meal%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou're%20probably%20already%20getting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprotein-mistakes-health-issues-hit-your-goals-without-wasting-money-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eenough%20protein%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20Ludwig%20said%2C%20but%20timing%20it%20correctly%20can%20help%20you%20feel%20full%20throughout%20the%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20stabilizes%20your%20blood%20sugars.%20It%20keeps%20you%20feeling%20fuller%20for%20longer%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BHaving%20your%20protein%20in%20the%20morning%20is%20really%20important%20because%20if%20you%20get%20breakfast%20right%2C%20it%20sets%20the%20bar%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20day.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20recommends%20aiming%20for%20around%2030%20grams%20of%20protein%20at%20each%20meal%20through%20sources%20like%20Greek%20yogurt%2C%20fish%2C%20chicken%2C%20or%20legumes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228256%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20close%20up%20of%20a%20woman%20meal%20prepping%20chicken%20and%20vegetables.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3194f0564c774507cd311e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225504%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EYou%20don't%20need%20to%20eat%20heaps%20of%20chicken%20breast%20to%20get%20enough%20protein.%20Start%20with%20around%2030%20grams%20per%20meal.%3Cp%3EFilmstax%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20about%2090%20grams%20of%20protein%20per%20day%2C%20although%20you%20may%20need%20more%20if%20you're%20larger%20or%20highly%20active.%20Research%20suggests%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-protein-maximize-muscle-gains-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eadults%20benefit%20from%3C%2Fa%3E%20around%201.5%20grams%20of%20protein%20per%20kilogram%20of%20body%20weight%20(or%200.7%20grams%20per%20pound)%20daily.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-protein-guidelines-how-to-eat-more-without-too-much-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eright%20amount%20of%20protein%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20also%20important%20for%20a%20long%2C%20healthy%20life%2C%20and%20we%20generally%20need%20more%20as%20we%20get%20older%20to%20prevent%20age-related%20loss%20of%20muscle%20tissue%20and%20promote%20a%20healthy%20metabolism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BProteins%20are%20not%20only%20for%20our%20muscles%2C%20but%20they're%20also%20for%20repair%2C%20they%20support%20our%20immune%20system%2C%20and%20our%20neurotransmitters.%20They're%20really%20important%2C%26quot%3B%20Ludwig%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22621f6c3b-bd9b-41b8-9dfc-a84e4d3f20ef%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAim%20for%2030%20grams%20of%20fiber%20a%20day%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20protein%20gets%20all%20the%20attention%2C%20Ludwig%20said%20fiber%20is%20an%20underrated%20nutrient%20that%20supports%20gut%20health%2C%20weight%20loss%2C%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20living%20in%20this%20massive%20fiber%20gap%20at%20the%20moment%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20missing%20link.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-eat-more-fiber-tips-plant-based-cardiologist-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eenough%20fiber%3C%2Fa%3E%20helps%20slow%20digestion%2C%20which%20can%20promote%20steadier%20blood%20sugar%20and%20energy%20levels%2C%20helping%20you%20feel%20more%20satisfied%20after%20meals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225616%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20whole%20grain%20sandwich%20on%20a%20cutting%20board%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3194a22bbd1d834ef2434e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223744%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EProtein%20and%20fiber%20work%20together%20to%20keep%20you%20full%20after%20meals.%20Try%20combos%20like%20whole-grain%20bread%20and%20chicken%20or%20tuna%20salad%2C%20Greek%20yogurt%20with%20berries%20and%20nuts%2C%20or%20lentil%20soup%20with%20veggies.%3Cp%3Ebhofack2%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BProtein%20and%20fiber%20are%20like%20this%20dynamic%20duo%3B%20together%20they're%20bulky%2C%20and%20that%20means%20they%20switch%20on%20all%20these%20satiety%20mechanisms%2C%26quot%3B%20Ludwig%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20recommends%2030%20grams%20a%20day%2C%20slightly%20more%20than%20typical%20dietary%20advice%2C%20based%20on%20research%20from%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feat-30-plants-week-fiber-gut-health-time-saving-habits-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20Gut%20Project%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20study%20of%20more%20than%2015%2C000%20people%20led%20by%20the%20University%20of%20California%20San%20Diego%2C%20that%20analyzed%20health%20and%20eating%20habits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoctor-foods-more-fiber-lower-risk-colon-cancer-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EHigh-fiber%20diets%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20rich%20in%20foods%20like%20beans%2C%20nuts%2C%20and%20whole%20grains%20%E2%80%94%20are%20also%20linked%20to%20a%20lower%20risk%20of%20chronic%20illnesses%20like%20heart%20disease%20and%20colorectal%20cancer%2C%20making%20fiber%20a%20key%20nutrient%20for%20longevity%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22417505c5-99c7-4a4c-863a-47d5a5c1f6aa%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EInclude%20a%20variety%20of%20plants%20in%20your%20diet%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20final%2030%20in%20Ludwig's%20formula%20refers%20to%20including%2030%20different%20types%20of%20plants%20in%20your%20diet%20each%20week%2C%20to%20provide%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20nutrients%20for%20gut%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20digestive%20system%20hosts%20colonies%20of%20beneficial%20bacteria%2C%20your%20microbiome%2C%20which%20play%20a%20key%20role%20in%20health%2C%20from%20your%20mood%20to%20your%20energy%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELudwig%20compared%20the%20microbiome%20to%20a%20zoo%3A%20just%20as%20giraffes%20prefer%20different%20foods%20from%20lions%2C%20each%20type%20of%20gut%20microbe%20thrives%20on%20different%20micronutrients%20found%20in%20different%20plants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELoading%20up%20on%2030%20plants%20a%20week%20is%20easier%20than%20you%20might%20think%3A%20every%20little%20bit%20counts%2C%20from%20the%20herbs%20and%20spices%20in%20your%20pantry%20to%20your%20morning%20coffee%20or%20tea.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20she%20said%2C%20don't%20forget%20to%20treat%20yourself%3A%20fresh%20fruits%2C%20popcorn%2C%20and%20dark%20chocolate%20all%20help%20support%20a%20healthier%20gut%20in%20the%20long%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnutritionist-triple-30-rule-to-get-enough-protein-and-fiber-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1781697721000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3193d2564c774507cd310f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnutritionist-triple-30-rule-to-get-enough-protein-