20per%20a%20new%20report%20from%20the%20brand%20consultancy%20Lippincott.%3Cp%3EDNY59%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20version%20of%20this%20post%20appears%20in%20the%20CMO%20Insider%20newsletter.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESign%20up%20for%20%3Ca%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsubscription%2Fnewsletter%2Fcmo-insider%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider's%20weekly%20marketing%20newsletter%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EModern%20CMOs%20are%20getting%20the%20promotion%20they've%20long%20wanted%3A%20job%20titles%20like%20CGO%20that%20reflect%20their%20revenue%20and%20growth%20responsibilities.%20The%20catch%3F%20They're%20not%20getting%20more%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20a%20sharp%20tension%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20a%20new%20study%20shared%20exclusively%20with%20CMO%20Insider%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3Eby%20the%20brand%20consultancy%20Lippincott.%20The%20study%20analyzed%20a%20survey%20of%20541%20global%20CMOs%20or%20equivalents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20more%20responsibility%20but%20less%20of%20that%20autonomy%20in%20terms%20of%20getting%20a%20strong%20sense%20of%20alignment%20across%20the%20organization%2C%26quot%3B%20Michael%20D'Esopo%2C%20Lippincott%20CEO%2C%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%2080%25%20said%20bureaucracy%20commonly%20got%20in%20the%20way%20of%20decision-making%2C%20while%2084%25%20said%20it%20was%20at%20least%20%26quot%3Bsomewhat%20difficult%26quot%3B%20to%20align%20their%20management%20team%2C%20senior%20peers%2C%20and%20other%20stakeholders%20around%20a%20marketing%20vision.%20Fewer%20than%20half%20(44%25)%20said%20marketing%20operated%20with%20high%20autonomy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FYhg5j%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Bar%20Chart%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FYhg5j%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20unnamed%20CMO%20quoted%20in%20the%20report%20put%20it%20this%20way%3A%20%26quot%3BWhat%20often%20happens%20is%20that%20a%20strong%2C%20well-founded%20idea%20gets%20gradually%20diluted.%20Someone%20senior%2C%20like%20a%20CFO%20or%20CCO%2C%20adds%20input%20that%20doesn't%20align%20with%20the%20evidence%2C%20and%20people%20hesitate%20to%20challenge%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20issue%20is%20that%20many%20CEOs%20aren't%20confident%20in%20marketing's%20ability%20to%20demonstrate%20a%20financial%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20huge%20trust%20problem%20for%20marketing%20in%20the%20C-suite%2C%26quot%3B%20former%20Mastercard%20CMO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-cmos-can-navigate-marketing-through-turbulent-times-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ERaja%20Rajamannar%3C%2Fa%3E%20told%20me%20in%20a%20recent%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlenty%20of%20studies%20over%20the%20years%20have%20suggested%20marketing%20has%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceos-dont-trust-cmos-according-to-a-new-industry-report-2021-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecredibility%20problem%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20corner%20office.%20A%20report%20released%20in%20April%20from%20the%20communications%20firm%20Boathouse%2C%20for%20example%2C%20found%20only%2013%25%20of%20CEOs%20were%20confident%20in%20marketing's%20ability%20to%20demonstrate%20a%20financial%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20long-held%20tensions%20are%20being%20exacerbated%20by%20technological%20shifts%2C%20D'Esopo%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20abundance%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarketing-chief-exec-ai-creativity-boom-not-job-threat-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI-powered%20dashboards%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20analytics%20tools%20has%20made%20marketing%20performance%20more%20visible%20across%20organizations%2C%20D'Esopo%20said.%20That%20can%20help%20CMOs%20appeal%20to%20finance%20leaders%20by%20showcasing%20short-term%20wins%2C%20but%20it%20can%20also%20reinforce%20a%20focus%20on%20immediate%20results%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20long-term%20brand%20building.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20new%20tools%20have%20also%20boosted%20marketing%20leaders%20who%20are%20steeped%20in%20data.%20Lippincott%20said%2035%25%20of%20marketing%20chiefs%20come%20from%20performance-%20or%20growth-marketing%20backgrounds.%20Around%2020%25%20of%20the%20senior-most%20marketing%20decision-makers%20don't%20even%20have%20%26quot%3Bmarketing%26quot%3B%20in%20their%20job%20title%2C%20reflecting%20the%20rise%20of%20chief%20growth%2C%20chief%20revenue%2C%20and%20chief%20commercial%20officers%2C%20per%20Lippincott.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20can%20have%20both%20good%20and%20bad%20effects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rise%20of%20performance-minded%20leaders%20may%20bring%20more%20analytical%20rigor%20to%20balance%20out%20softer%20marketing%20metrics.%20However%2C%20Rajamannar%20said%20they%20can%20use%20a%20brute-force%20approach%2C%20likening%20it%20to%20%26quot%3Brunning%20constantly%20on%20the%20treadmill.%26quot%3B%20It%20can%20lead%20to%20chasing%20the%20next%20click%2C%20lead%2C%20or%20conversion%20rather%20than%20building%20the%20underlying%20consumer%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShort-termism%20is%20also%20creeping%20into%20new%20areas%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-search-strategies-hampered-by-corporate-silos-semrush-study-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20search%20visibility%3C%2Fa%3E.%20CMOs%20surveyed%20said%20their%20companies%20are%20spending%20more%20on%20AI%20while%20cutting%20investment%20in%20websites%20and%20content%20%E2%80%94%20the%20very%20assets%20AI%20systems%20use%20to%20understand%20and%20surface%20brands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20if%20that's%20the%20diagnosis%2C%20what's%20the%20antidote%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELippincott%20said%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lippincott.com%2Fcmo-outlook-2026%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20CMOs%20need%20to%20use%20the%20language%20of%20business%20growth%20without%20losing%20the%20fundamentals%20of%20long-term%20brand%20building%2C%20which%20may%20require%20translating%20marketing's%20impact%20differently%20for%20each%20separate%20stakeholder%2C%20whether%20that's%20the%20CEO%2C%20CFO%2C%20or%20the%20board.%20And%20organizational%20alignment%20should%20be%20treated%20as%20a%20growth%20strategy%20in%20its%20own%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fglobal-consumer-marketing-officer-jane-wakely-pepsico-sports-cannes-lions-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPepsiCo's%20Jane%20Wakely%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20has%20possibly%20the%20longest%20job%20title%20in%20the%20marketing%20profession%20%E2%80%94%20executive%20vice%20president%2C%20chief%20consumer%20and%20marketing%20officer%2C%20and%20chief%20growth%20officer%20for%20international%20foods%20%E2%80%94%20said%20CMOs%20should%20stay%20focused%20on%20the%20marketing%20principles%20that%20don't%20change.%20New%20technologies%20such%20as%20AI%20and%20diverse%20data%20sources%20just%20give%20marketers%20more%20ways%20to%20achieve%20their%20goals%2C%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20I'm%20reaching%20a%20billion%20people%20every%20day%2C%20to%20grow%20I've%20got%20to%20reach%20more%20than%20a%20billion%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20quite%20simple%2C%26quot%3B%20Wakely%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20is%20not%20going%20to%20change.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flippincott-study-cmos-more-responsibility-less-power-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1781696966000%2C%22visu