src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a31c5cd4074dae0e20446c7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%226336%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENew%20menu%20items%20at%20Panera%20Bread%20this%20summer%20include%20its%20Carnitas%20Elote%20bowl%2C%20pictured%20above%20with%20the%20chain's%20popular%20Mexican%20Street%20Corn%20Chowder.%3Cp%3EPanera%20Bread%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECarbone%20said%20Panera%20began%20developing%20the%20strategy%20last%20year%20after%20multiple%20years%20of%20negative%20same-store%20transactions.%20Sales%20sometimes%20rose%2C%20he%20said%2C%20but%20that%20growth%20was%20driven%20by%20pricing%20and%20mix%2C%20not%20by%20more%20customers%20coming%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20lifeblood%20of%20a%20restaurant%20company%20is%20transactions%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20that's%20where%20we%20started%20to%20develop%20Panera%20RISE.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20its%20core%2C%20RISE%20is%20Panera's%20attempt%20to%20fix%20the%20complaints%20customers%20raised%20most%20often%3A%20food%20that%20no%20longer%20felt%20worth%20the%20price%2C%20fewer%20affordable%20options%2C%20weaker%20in-store%20service%2C%20and%20growing%20competition%20for%20diners'%20attention.%20The%20company%20spent%20months%20talking%20with%20thousands%20of%20customers%20to%20determine%20its%20areas%20of%20focus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarbone%20said%20many%20still%20had%20warm%20feelings%20toward%20Panera%2C%20but%20had%20stopped%20visiting%20because%20the%20chain%20had%20gotten%20too%20expensive%2C%20removed%20favorite%20menu%20items%2C%20or%20simply%20fallen%20out%20of%20their%20routines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20a%20tough%20place%20to%20be%20in%20a%20restaurant%20market%20where%20consumers%20have%20become%20increasingly%20selective.%20Business%20Insider%20has%20previously%20reported%20that%20diners%20are%20splitting%20along%20income%20lines%2C%20with%20lower-income%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwealthy-americans-spend-lower-income-cut-back-affordability-earnings-consumers-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Econsumers%20cutting%20back%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20wealthier%20households%20keep%20spending.%20Restaurants%20have%20responded%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-k-shaped-economy-breaking-fast-food-playbook-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ediscounts%20and%20limited-time%20offers%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20improve%20value%20messaging%2C%20but%20analysts%20have%20warned%20that%20value%20alone%20is%20not%20always%20enough%20to%20bring%20customers%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPanera's%20own%20traffic%20remains%20under%20intense%20pressure.%20Foot%20traffic%20has%20declined%20year%20over%20year%20every%20month%20from%20January%20through%20May%20this%20year%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20the%20foot%20traffic%20firm%2C%20Placer.ai.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ER.J.%20Hottovy%2C%20Placer.ai's%20head%20of%20analytical%20research%2C%20said%20sandwich%20chains%20in%20particular%20have%20seen%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efewer%20visits%20than%20other%20concepts%20as%20consumers%20push%20back%20on%20menu%20price%20increases%20and%20embrace%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsteak-n-shake-maga-rfk-tallow-tesla-bitcoin-fast-food-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehealthier%20eating%20habits%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarbone's%20diagnosis%20goes%20beyond%20food.%20Panera%20also%20cut%20labor%20at%20caf%C3%A9s%20to%20cut%20costs%2C%20he%20said.%20The%20company%20has%20since%20added%20a%20front-of-house%20role%2C%20the%20Guest%20Experience%20Champion%2C%20to%20greet%20customers%2C%20answer%20questions%2C%20and%20help%20maintain%20dining%20rooms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20also%20rethinking%20how%20technology%20fits%20into%20the%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20was%20a%20time%20that%20if%20you%20talked%20to%20folks%20here%2C%20they%20would%20tell%20you%20that%20we%20were%20a%20technology%20company%20that%20sold%20food%2C%26quot%3B%20Carbone%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20will%20tell%20you%20emphatically%2C%20we%20are%20a%20restaurant%20company%20that%20uses%20technology%20to%20enhance%20the%20guest%20experience.%20We're%20not%20a%20technology%20company.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20does%20not%20mean%20abandoning%20digital%20ordering%2C%20kiosks%2C%20or%20loyalty%20tools.%20Only%20about%20a%20quarter%20of%20Panera's%20business%20is%20now%20eaten%20inside%20its%20caf%C3%A9s%2C%20Carbone%20said%2C%20but%20two-thirds%20of%20customers%20still%20walk%20into%20a%20restaurant%2C%20whether%20they%20are%20dining%20in%2C%20picking%20up%2C%20or%20ordering%20to%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20the%20in-store%20experience%20still%20matters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20RISE%2C%20Panera%20is%20adding%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fafter-opening-over-25-restaurants-id-make-one-big-menu-change-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enew%20menu%20items%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20drinks%2C%20but%20the%20bigger%20bet%20is%20that%20customers%20will%20notice%20when%20the%20chain%20starts%20optimizing%20for%20experience%20again%2C%20not%20just%20efficiency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarbone%20said%20Panera's%20priorities%20now%20are%20simple%3A%20%26quot%3BTransactions%2C%20sales%2C%20profits%20%E2%80%94%20in%20that%20order.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20years%20of%20trying%20to%20drive%20growth%20through%20price%20cuts%20and%20efficiency%2C%20Panera%20is%20betting%20that%20getting%20more%20customers%20through%20the%20door%20again%20will%20take%20something%20simpler%3A%20giving%20them%20a%20reason%20to%20come%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpanera-rise-revitalization-strategy-revamps-summer-menu-boost-customer-visits-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1781690403000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a31c5074074dae0e20446bc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22o