t%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f791931e-9dbf-4576-bce7-658874a89927%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAI%20spending%20also%20continues%20to%20soar%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETechnology%20and%20media%20companies%20spent%20an%20average%20of%20%2466.29%20per%20employee%20on%20AI%20in%20May%2C%20up%20from%20%2458.84%20in%20April%2C%20according%20to%20Ramp's%20AI%20Index.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAra%20Kharazian%2C%20its%20lead%20economist%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20he%20expected%20this%20metric%20to%20keep%20rising%2C%20but%20he%20spotted%20early%20signs%20of%20tightening%2C%20such%20as%20increased%20use%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-routing-startups-openrouter-concentrate-funding-boom-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emodel%20routers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20can%20help%20better%20manage%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20companies%20aren't%20cutting%20AI%20budgets%20just%20yet%2C%20but%20they%20are%20thinking%20critically%20about%20head%20count.%20For%20instance%2C%20MindFort%2C%20a%20Y%20Combinator-backed%20AI%20startup%2C%20has%20six%20employees.%20Its%20CEO%2C%20Brandon%20Veiseh%2C%20said%20the%20company%20would've%20needed%2020%20employees%20pre-AI%20to%20reach%20its%20current%20scale.%20Where%20have%20those%20funds%20gone%3F%20Tokens.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227008%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22MindFort%20CEO%20Brandon%20Veiseh%20is%20pictured.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3070a39ab49a56117200ad%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224672%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBrandon%20Veiseh%20is%20focused%20on%20getting%20a%20return%20on%20investment%20on%20AI%20spend%20at%20his%20company.%3Cp%3EMorgan%20Lieberman%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20to%20weigh%20our%20token-to-people%20ratio%2C%26quot%3B%20Veiseh%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20something%20we%20think%20is%20particularly%20comfortable%20or%20a%20great%20feeling%20to%20say.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20token%20costs%20are%20expected%20to%20come%20down%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ai-cost-tokens-gemini-flash-openai-anthropic-gemini-search-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20companies%20like%20Google%3C%2Fa%3E%20increasingly%20compete%20on%20price%20by%20offering%20smaller%2C%20more%20efficient%20models%2C%20these%20sorts%20of%20tradeoffs%20aren't%20likely%20to%20go%20away.%20Often%2C%20the%20cheaper%20a%20resource%20is%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-job-market-labor-unemployment-jevons-paradox-apollo-torsten-slok-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20more%20of%20it%20is%20consumed%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20companies%20are%20thinking%20more%20critically%20and%20sometimes%20taking%20strategic%20steps%20back%20%E2%80%94%20but%20they're%20hesitant%20to%20move%20too%20quickly.%20Kausas%2C%20Pylon's%20CEO%2C%20said%20he%20wants%20to%20prioritize%20making%20sure%20there's%20a%20return%20on%20investment%20%E2%80%94%20and%20avoid%20engineer%20backlash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20told%20engineers%20that%20they%20were%20not%20allowed%20to%20use%20AI%20products%2C%20they%20would%20not%20work%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20would%20feel%20like%20you%20were%20in%20the%20Stone%20Age.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f5e807f1-901e-4abf-b36d-b5189c55b975%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDawn%20of%20the%20token%20Hunger%20Games%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20engineers%20increasingly%20learn%20they%20might%20have%20to%20battle%20for%20their%20token%20allocation%2C%20team%20infighting%20could%20grow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20have%20compared%20this%20to%20a%20survival-of-the-fittest%20scenario.%20%26quot%3BCoding%20is%20now%20cockroach%20protein%20bars%20and%20we're%20all%20fighting%20for%20crumbs%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20coder%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2F0xRizzler%2Fstatus%2F2064010754068787614%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eon%20X%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20comparing%20the%20dynamic%20to%20%26quot%3BThe%20Hunger%20Games.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDevelopers%20are%20also%20asking%20more%20about%20tokens%20during%20job%20interviews.%20Kausas%20said%20that%20applicants%20had%20asked%20him%20about%20budgets.%20AI%20advisor%20and%20AWS%20alum%20Allie%20K.%20Miller%20had%20heard%20of%20interviewees%20getting%20into%20the%20nitty-gritty%3A%20%26quot%3BWhat%20tier%20of%20model%20will%20I%20have%20access%20to%3F%20Do%20you%20have%20partnerships%20with%20AI%20labs%20that%20get%20us%20relatively%20early%20access%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227008%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22MindFort%20CEO%20Brandon%20Veiseh%20and%20his%20employee%2C%20Daniel%20Rabinovich%2C%20are%20pictured.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3070d89ab49a56117200b1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224672%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20to%20weigh%20our%20token-to-people%20ratio%2C%26quot%3B%20Veiseh%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20something%20we%20think%20is%20particularly%20comfortable%20or%20a%20great%20feeling%20to%20say.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EMorgan%20Lieberman%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20sign%20of%20a%20new%20era%20where%20tokens%20%E2%80%94%20or%20at%20least%20the%20number%20workers%20want%20%E2%80%94%20aren't%20guaranteed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMax%20Christoff%2C%20the%20CTO%20of%20legal%20tech%20company%20Everlaw%2C%20made%20the%20case%20for%20giving%20engineers%20token%20caps%2C%20but%20letting%20them%20negotiate%20for%20bigger%20budgets.%20He%20compared%20it%20to%20using%20cellular%20data%20before%20unlimited%20plans.%20Sometimes%20you%20need%20to%20spend%20big%20on%20the%20data%2C%20but%20other%20times%20you%20mindlessly%20scroll%2C%20not%20realizing%20how%20much%20you're%20wasting.%20Christoff%20wanted%20all%20of%20the%20former%20and%20none%20of%20the%20latter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20make%20it%20easy%20to%20ask%20for%20more%20if%20you%20can%20actually%20use%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Christoff%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20company%20doesn't%20set%20token%20caps%2C%20it%20may%20also%20set%20model%20restrictions.%20Russ%20Franklin%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Larridin%2C%20a%20platform%20for%20tracking%20AI%20use%2C%20was%20emphatic.%20%26quot%3BOf%20course%2C%20they%20will%20limit%20who%20gets%20to%20use%20these%20tools.%20It's%20not%20even%20a%20question%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFranklin%20compared%20allocating%20model%20access%20to%20taking%20a%20trip%20on%20the%20company%20dime.%20Many%20are%20allowed%20to%20book%20an%20economy%20flight%2C%20but%20few%20%E2%80%94%20if%20any%20%E2%80%94%20are%20allowed%20to%20charter%20a%20jet%2C%20he%20said.%20Access%20to%20cutting-edge%20AI%20models%20may%20be%20equivalent%20to%20the%20private%20jet%3A%20so%20expensive%20that%20only%20a%20few%20all-stars%20can%20do%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEngineers%20have%20good%20reason%20to%20fight%20for%20their%20tokens.%20Having%20limited%20AI%20access%20could%20hurt%20them%20in%20the%20long%20run%2C%20leaving%20them%20less%20skilled%20or%20less%20marketable%20in%20future%20job%20searches.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrock%20Simon%20advised%20companies%20on%20AI%20for%20Bain%20%26amp%3B%20Company%20before%20he%20founded%20his%20own%20startup%2C%20Native.%20He%20watched%20as%20some%20companies%20were%20slow%20to%20adopt%20the%20technology%20or%20restricted%20access%20to%20specific%20tools%20and%20agents%2C%20leaving%20their%20employees%20behind%20the%20curve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20really%20hurt%20some%20people's%20careers%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%2F%2Fembed.typeform.com%2Fnext%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%20data-tf-live%3D%5C%2201KT4V1KSD7NAQBY7K1VBHHSCT%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-token-economy-spending-workplace-budgets-usage-caps-software-engineer-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1781688602000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a306c770b873a3c9460d14a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-token-economy-spending-workplace-budgets-usage-caps-software-engineer-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22AI%20token%20spending%20soared%20from%20companies%20pushing%20unlimited%20use%2C%20but%20tech%20workers%20are%20now%20competing%20for%20compute%20as%20companies%20rethink%20budgets.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22hchandonnet%40insider.com%20(Henry%20Chandonnet)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22One%20of%20legal's%20hottest%20startups%20is%20helping%20lawyers%20finally%20answer%3A%20Is%20the%20AI's%20work%20any%20good%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226698%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20people%20stand%20on%20a%20quiet%20urban%20street%20lined%20with%20brick%20buildings%2C%20both%20facing%20the%20camera.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3192ee564c774507cd30f9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225023%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERyan%20Daniels%20and%20John%20Sarihan.%3Cp%3ECrosby%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EBillions%20of%20dollars%20are%20riding%20on%20the%20promise%20that%20artificial%20intelligence%20can%20absorb%20legal%20work.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECrosby%2C%20a%20tech-driven%20law%20firm%2C%20built%20a%20benchmark%20to%20measure%20how%20well%20models%20negotiate%20contracts.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERedline%20Bench%20is%20meant%20to%20help%20lawyers%20answer%20whether%20they%20can%20trust%20the%20technology's%20work.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ELegal%20technology%20wants%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-coding-agents-tools-software-engineering-jobs-future-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Evibe-coding%3C%2Fa%3E%20moment.%20But%20first%2C%20it%20has%20to%20prove%20the%20tools%20can%20think%20like%20a%20lawyer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETaking%20up%20the%20task%20is%20Crosby%2C%20a%20startup-meets-law-firm%20that%20sells%20basic%20legal%20services%20to%20companies%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcursor-ceo-michael-truell-spacex-elon-musk-anthropic-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECursor%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Rogo.%20On%20Wednesday%2C%20it%20released%20the%20Redline%20Bench%2C%20a%20tool%20built%20to%20measure%20how%20well%20artificial%20intelligence%20models%20perform%20real-world%20legal%20tasks%2C%20starting%20with%20contract%20review.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoftware%20engineers%20have%20spent%20the%20past%20few%20years%20watching%20these%20systems%20get%20shockingly%20good%20at%20writing%20code%20and%20debugging%20errors.%20Now%20legal%20tech%20companies%20are%20chasing%20a%20similar%20prize%3A%20artificial%20intelligence%20that%20can%20review%20contracts%2C%20spot%20risks%2C%20and%20haggle%20terms%20faster%20and%20cheaper%20than%20lawyers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20law%20has%20a%20problem%20that%20coding%20does%20not%2C%20says%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcrosby-ceo-job-interview-work-trial-sunday-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ERyan%20Daniels%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20former%20in-house%20lawyer%20turned%20Crosby%20founder.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20hard%20to%20define%20'good'%20or%20'bad%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EModels%20can%20write%20code%20that%20either%20runs%20or%20breaks.%20Legal%20work%20is%20a%20murkier%20target.%20A%20sales%20contract%20can%20be%20edited%2C%20or%20%26quot%3Bredlined%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20lots%20of%20defensible%20ways%2C%20Daniels%20explains.%20A%20change%20that%20one%20lawyer%20sees%20as%20prudent%2C%20another%20might%20call%20too%20aggressive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20ambiguity%20has%20become%20a%20headache%20for%20companies%20racing%20to%20automate%20legal%20work%2C%20from%20the%20scrappy%20neofirms%20to%20the%20model%20labs%20themselves.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-legal-ai-tool-plugin-competition-lexisnexis-thomson-reuters-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAnthropic%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20spent%20the%20past%20few%20months%20courting%20in-house%20lawyers%20with%20tools%20built%20for%20them.%20That%20push%20has%20been%20closely%20watched%20by%20investors.%20Earlier%20this%20year%2C%20Anthropic's%20new%20legal%20plugin%20stirred%20a%20sell-off%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-cowork-legal-plugin-publishing-stocks-legalzoom-thomson-reuters-relx-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elegal%20tech%20stocks%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBenchmarks%20are%20one%20of%20the%20main%20ways%20companies%20track%20progress.%20The%20labs%20building%20frontier%20models%20use%20them%20as%20stress%20tests%2C%20measuring%20whether%20a%20new%20system%20is%20better%20at%20tasks%20than%20the%20last%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECoding%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fhtml%2F2503.05860v2%23S1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehundreds%20of%20benchmarks%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20evaluating%20models.%20But%20the%20legal%20industry%20still%20lacks%20a%20shared%20way%20to%20answer%20the%20question%3A%20Is%20the%20AI's%20work%20any%20good%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECrosby%20has%20been%20working%20on%20a%20new%20yardstick.%20The%20company%20pulled%20its%20engineers%20and%20lawyers%20into%20a%20tactical%20unit%20called%20Crosby%20Intelligence%20to%20build%20agents%20for%20Crosby's%20law%20firm%20and%20a%20benchmark%20to%20grade%20them%20against.%20That%20team%20includes%20engineer%20Sharan%20Ramjee%2C%20who%20worked%20on%20transformer%20models%20to%20sniff%20out%20fraud%20at%20Stripe%2C%20and%20Ross%20Weiser%2C%20a%20lawyer%20who%20joined%20from%20elite%20law%20firm%20Sullivan%20%26amp%3B%20Cromwell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228247%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20people%20in%20dark%20clothing%20walk%20together%20on%20a%20city%20sidewalk%20beside%20tall%20buildings.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a31a0564074dae0e20444d5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%226185%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ECrosby%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECrosby%20also%20partnered%20with%20Micro1%2C%20a%20company%20that%20helps%20model-makers%20recruit%20expert%20workers%2C%20to%20find%20more%20lawyers%20who%20could%20help%20define%20what%20counts%20as%20good%20legal%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20build%20the%20benchmark%2C%20senior%20lawyers%20simulated%20software%20deals%20and%20marked%20the%20contract%20changes%20they%20considered%20most%20important%20at%20each%20stage%20of%20the%20negotiation.%20Those%20changes%20were%20turned%20into%20weighted%20criteria.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Crosby%20runs%20a%20new%20test%2C%20it%20gives%20models%20the%20same%20contracts%20and%20asks%20them%20to%20make%20their%20own%20edits.%20Then%20a%20panel%20of%20three%20judges%20compares%20these%20redlines%20with%20the%20lawyer-built%20rubric.%20The%20judges%20vote%20pass%20or%20fail%20on%20each%20item%2C%20and%20the%20final%20score%20shows%20how%20often%20the%20models%20made%20the%20kinds%20of%20edits%20that%20lawyers%20considered%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERedline%20Bench%20will%20be%20made%20public%20so%20any%20lab%20can%20put%20its%20models%20through%20Crosby's%20paces.%20Crosby%20also%20plans%20to%20regularly%20release%20reports%20tracking%20how%20major%20models%20compare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20release%20of%20the%20Redline%20Bench%20put%20ChatGPT%205.5%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20heap%2C%20with%20a%20score%20of%2050.5%25%2C%20meaning%20the%20model's%20redlines%20matched%20half%20of%20the%20edits%20that%20lawyers%20prioritized.%20Gemini%203.5%20Flash%20followed%20at%2045.1%25%2C%20and%20Claude%20Opus%204.8%20scored%2044.4%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECrosby%20was%20able%20to%20test%20Anthropic's%20highly%20capable%20new%20model%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-white-house-ordered-export-controls-anthropic-mythos-fable-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EFable%205%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20only%20once%20before%20Anthropic%20pulled%20it%20off%20the%20shelves.%20The%20results%20were%20promising%2C%20with%20a%20score%20of%2047.3%25.%20When%20access%20is%20restored%2C%20Crosby%20will%20run%20the%20benchmark%20again%20and%20update%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20wearing%20earbuds%20smiles%20while%20working%20on%20a%20laptop%20from%20a%20couch%20in%20a%20quiet%2C%20sunlit%20office.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a319237564c774507cd30e6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERyan%20Daniels.%3Cp%3ECrosby%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECrosby%20isn't%20the%20only%20company%20trying%20to%20measure%20how%20the%20models%20stack%20up.%20Harvey%2C%20one%20of%20the%20best-funded%20legal%20startups%2C%20has%20released%20benchmarks%20for%20case%20law%20research%20and%20contract%20review.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnthropic%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-openai-lawyer-nicole-diaz-uses-ai-for-legal-work-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EOpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20build%20their%20own%20benchmarks%20to%20measure%20performance%20on%20real-world%20tasks.%20But%20Daniels%20said%20those%20results%20can%20be%20hard%20to%20trust.%20Over%20time%2C%20the%20labs%20eventually%20tune%20their%20systems%20to%20perform%20well%20on%20their%20own%20tests%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20stakes%20are%20bigger%20than%20a%20scoreboard.%20Billions%20of%20investment%20dollars%20are%20riding%20on%20the%20promise%20that%20artificial%20intelligence%20can%20lower%20legal%20bills%20and%20absorb%20work%20that%20used%20to%20pile%20up%20on%20the%20general%20counsel's%20desk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELawyers%20will%20only%20use%20the%20tools%20if%20they%20trust%20them.%20Crosby%20wants%20to%20give%20them%20a%20reason%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcrosby-releases-redline-bench-evaluate-ai-models-for-contract-review-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1781688601000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3192c64074dae0e20443fe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcrosby-releases-redline-bench-evaluate-ai-models-for-contract-review-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Legal%20AI%20startups%20say%20their%20tools%20can%20absorb%20routine%20work.%20Crosby%20is%20releasing%20a%20benchmark%20to%20test%20whether%20lawyers%20should%20trust%20them.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mrussell%40businessinsider.com%20(Melia%20Russell)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Sports%2C%20cigarettes%20and%20Greenland%3A%20What%20world%20leaders%20were%20caught%20discussing%20on%20G7%20hot%20mics%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1781688567000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-131794266%2Cimgsize-91270.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fsports-cigarettes-and-greenland-what-world-leaders-were-caught-discussing-on-g7-hot-mics%2Farticleshow%2F131793922.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F131793922.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20World%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fsports-