ers%20or%20taking%20outposts%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225472%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Three%20Ukrainian%20soldiers%20hold%20rifles%20while%20training%20for%20trench%20warfare%20in%20Sumy.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3257e64074dae0e20447f4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223648%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESoldiers%20in%20Sumy%20train%20in%20a%20trench%20during%20the%20winter.%3Cp%3EFrancisco%20Richart%20Barbeira%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EUkrainian%20troops%20on%20the%20front%20lines%20can%20earn%20up%20to%20%2410%2C270%20a%20month%20based%20on%20how%20much%20they%20fight.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThat's%20nearly%2030%20times%20the%20average%20salary%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20bonuses%20are%20part%20of%20a%20new%20push%20to%20overhaul%20Ukraine's%20pay%20and%20contract%20system.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20is%20implementing%20a%20new%20bonus%20system%20that%20rewards%20frontline%20troops%20with%20cash%20for%20feats%20in%20battle%20or%20carrying%20out%20combat%20missions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20incentives%20are%20part%20of%20a%20salary%20and%20contract%20overhaul%20announced%20on%20June%2012%2C%20after%20years%20of%20Kyiv%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-exploiting-ukraine-manpower-shortage-thin-line-breakthrough-war-expert-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estruggling%20with%20recruitment%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20reports%20of%20absence%20without%20leave%2C%20or%20AWOL.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20defense%20ministry%20said%20on%20Tuesday%20that%20the%20new%20system%20would%20apply%20to%20combat%20missions%20or%20tasks%20from%20the%20start%20of%20June%2C%20with%20payouts%20to%20be%20received%20in%20July.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20highest%20bonuses%20vary%20based%20on%20performance%2C%20and%20primarily%20apply%20to%20troops%20in%20the%20most%20dangerous%20roles%2C%20such%20as%20assault%20infantry%2C%20combat%20medics%2C%20and%20gunners.%20Each%20frontline%20soldier%20gets%20a%20base%20monthly%20pay%20of%2020%2C000%20hryvnias%2C%20or%20%24446%2C%20but%20could%20earn%20up%20to%20460%2C000%20hryvnias%2C%20or%20%2410%2C270%2C%20a%20month%20based%20on%20their%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20full%20payout%20would%20be%20nearly%2030%20times%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-pay-civilians-shoot-down-drones-own-guns-cars-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eaverage%20salary%20in%20Ukraine%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20the%20war%20began%3B%20government%20statistics%20from%20January%202022%20said%20the%20country's%20average%20monthly%20salary%20was%2014%2C577%20hryvnias.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20day%20at%20a%20Ukrainian-held%20position%20earns%20the%20soldier%20another%2010%2C000%20hryvnias%2C%20while%20each%20day%20carrying%20out%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-convict-soldiers-troops-ukraine-war-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emore%20aggressive%20missions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20such%20as%20reconnaissance%2C%20evacuation%2C%20or%20recapturing%20friendly%20territory%2C%20nets%20them%2020%2C000%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20daily%20bonus%20is%2040%2C000%20hryvnias%20for%20each%20day%20spent%20in%20assault%20operations%20that%20result%20in%20a%20Ukrainian%20advance.%20The%20bonuses%20don't%20stack%2C%20so%20a%20soldier%20can%20only%20earn%20one%20per%20day%20%E2%80%94%20whichever%20is%20highest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20there%20are%20bonuses%20for%20taking%20a%20Russian%20soldier%20prisoner%2C%20which%20is%20100%2C000%20hryvnias%20split%20among%20all%20troops%20involved%20directly%20in%20the%20capture%2C%20and%20destroying%20an%20enemy%20asset%20or%20killing%20a%20Russian%20soldier%2C%20which%20is%20worth%2015%2C000%20hryvnias.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECommanders%20and%20their%20teams%20can%20earn%20an%20extra%2030%2C000%20hryvnias%20a%20month%20for%20performing%20combat%20tasks%2C%20and%2050%2C000%20hryvnias%20for%20running%20operations%20from%20command%20posts%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20time%20they%20spent%20on%20missions%20that%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20grand%20total%20of%20these%20payments%20is%20capped%20at%20460%2C000%20a%20month%2C%20the%20Ukrainian%20defense%20ministry%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20stationed%20temporarily%20in%20rear%20areas%2C%20troops%20instead%20receive%20a%20minimum%20monthly%20pay%20of%2030%2C000%20hryvnias.%20Ukrainian%20soldiers%20regularly%20rotate%20between%20fighting%20near%20or%20at%20the%20front%20lines%20and%20resting%20in%20safer%20towns%20and%20strongholds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrone%20pilots'%20and%20specialists'%20salaries%20are%20different%2C%20with%20a%20scale%20that%20pays%20more%20the%20closer%20they%20are%20to%20the%20front%20lines%2C%20up%20to%20a%20maximum%20of%20120%2C000%20hryvnias.%20They%20can%20also%20get%20bonuses%20of%20up%20to%20100%2C000%20hryvnias%20for%20participating%20in%20combat%20or%20performing%20command%20roles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20defense%20ministry%20said%20it%20was%20also%20implementing%20a%20new%20system%20that%20allows%20troops%20who%20have%20gone%20AWOL%20to%20return%20to%20the%20military%20under%20the%20best-rated%20units%20and%20immediately%20receive%20gear%2C%20meals%2C%20and%20clothing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20measure%20seeks%20to%20fix%20a%20loophole%20that%20led%20dissatisfied%20Ukrainian%20troops%20to%20avoid%20the%20bureaucracy%20of%20applying%20for%20transfers%20and%20force%20a%20move%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-mykhailo-fedorov-troop-shortage-awol-draft-dodging-2-million-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eby%20going%20AWOL.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine's%20defense%20ministry%20has%20embarked%20on%20an%20aggressive%20overhaul%20since%20January%20under%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmykhailo-fedorov-advisors-defense-ministry-serhii-flash-sternenko-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMykhailo%20Fedorov%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20was%20appointed%20to%20lead%20the%20ministry%20after%20a%20stint%20as%20the%20country's%20minister%20for%20digital%20transformation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2035-year-old%20has%20pledged%20to%20address%20many%20of%20the%20systemic%20issues%20and%20gripes%20that%20have%20plagued%20Ukraine's%20forces%20for%20years%2C%20including%20low%20morale%20and%20lack%20of%20command%20transparency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20only%20the%20first%20stage%20of%20the%20comprehensive%20transformation%20of%20the%20Defense%20Forces%20of%20Ukraine%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20ministry%20said%20on%20June%2012.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-troops-monthly-bonus-capture-positions-outposts-10000-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1781688399000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a32599d4074dae0e20447f6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-troops-monthly-bonus-capture-positions-outposts-10000-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20new%20salary%20cap%20for%20Ukrainian%20frontline%20troops%20is%20worth%20about%2030%20times%20the%20average%20pay%20in%20the%20country%20before%20the%20war%20began.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mloh%40businessinsider.com%20(Matthew%20Loh)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20Portugal%20sign%20visa%20exemption%20deal%20for%20diplomatic%20and%20special%20passport%20holders%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1781688325000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-131794196%2Cimgsize-994932.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fsaudi-arabia-portugal-sign-visa-exemption-deal-for-diplomatic-and-special-passport-holders%2Farticleshow%2F131794192.cms%22%2C%22summar